<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Blizzard has a reputation for making quality games, and releasing quality. Im very happy with my gametime in WoW atm, but Im not saying the product doesnt have flaws. The server stability is still an issue that should be solved. Its partly players fault, its partly Blizzards fault. The content for level 60s is another issue, but if you actually do the content 1-60, youll be hardpressed to say there is a lack thereof. Right now, the major issue with content is "we only have X amt of high level dungeons to raid." Well, Im reaching that stage of the game for high level dungeons, but its not like Im going to be available to do these dungeons 24/7 so my interest will be peaked for quite some time in doing those expeditions.
<br />

<br />
WoW isnt getting any break. People are complaining. And Im not talking about the Official Forums. Even here at TheRunes people comment about WoW and its flaws. However, we keep our discussion in WoW Discussion, or to ourselves on other boards, partly because the moment ANYTHING negative is said about WoW here the community would have no problem saying, "see see see WoW sucks just as much as EQ, ya dang hypocrite." WoW has its problems, but Im forgiving towards WoW because Blizzard IS new to the MMORPG market and still have a chance to really make a difference with their product. I mean REALLY make a difference.
<br />

<br />
SoE had a chance to redeem my interest in Omens of War. I actually enjoyed that expansion, until WoW & EQ2 released. I could no longer enjoy that expansion afterwards because the people available to survive the zones I hunted and the Trials I partook in were gone to play these new venues (most of whom, never returned). Server population dropped, and there I was sitting with thumbs up my ass waiting for everyone to recouperate guild numbers, regear, and reflag to enjoy OoWs content. I dont have time to invest in sitting in PoK for nine hours LFG (yes I used the LFG tool quite a bit), or buffwhoring KEI. I just cant.
<br />

<br />
If you look at the performance of SoE since The Summit, youll see the playerbase has indeed plummeted on various servers, enough so that SoE decided to start merging them. SoE only makes attempts to talk with the playerbase when all other modes of desperation have failed. "Uh oh people are unhappy with GoD, we need a solution, THE SUMMIT!" "Uh oh, people have seen through our scheme, I know, COMMUNITY CORRESPONDANTS!" "Uh oh, people are realizing we have no intent of really doing anything on the Top 10 List, I know, TELLM AFTER THE NEXT EXPANSION." "Uh oh, people are actually leaving the game. I know, lets MERGE THE SERVERS." 
<br />

<br />
Blizzard IS more open, in the fact they actually started communication from Day One. SoE hasnt communicated squat until they realized their not the only game in town anymore. SoE made attempts, half-assed or otherwise, because they had NO CHOICE. Blizzard came onto the scene, and did it without question. SoE had to be backed into a corner before they would communicate with us, and even so, here we are with worthless Top 10 Lists and Class Correspondants whose job is pointless. Im forgiving of WoW because theyve shown since Day One they care. Their track record of games show they care. Their Devs care. 
<br />

<br />
Those of us who cared about EQ1, I mean TRULY cared about EQ1, are almost gone. That is why we say, and I say, that EQ1 is dead. Because the people SoE truly captivated with their game, they drove away. All thats left now is a pathetic attempt to compete with newcomers who did 95% of it right the moment their game was released, and just need to fix that extra 5% to put them over the top. Why would I support a company that after six years managed to taint the entire enjoyment of a game like Everquest that I truly loved playing and play EQ2, when its just more of the same with flashier graphics? Just because SoE may have "got it right" with EQ2 so to speak, doesnt mean its a whole new company policy in my eyes.
<br />

<br />
Ive played EQ1, EQ2, and WoW. Of all those, Im only subscribed to EQ1 and WoW. Of those choices, the only one Im playing IS WoW. What do I do with my EQ subscription for the last six and a half months? Chat. The game has evolved to "push out expansion after expansion, ignore class issues, more timesinks, less quality and more quantity," than actually making a fun, enjoyable environment. In the coming months, if Blizzard doesnt get off their duffs and get their ducks in a row, youll see the same complaints coming outta my mouth about them as I do about SoE. The big difference is Sony had six years to get off their ass and do something. Waiting until the last minute isnt a sign they care. Its a sign of desperation. Thats why Im overly critical of SoE, and why Im forgiving of Blizzard.
<br />

<br />
For now.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
