<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Badmorda, the difference....
<br />

<br />
There's a post like <a href="http://forums.worldofwarcraft.com/thread.aspx?fn=wow-hunter&t=169071&p=1&tmp=1#post169071" target="_blank" class="postlink">this</a> in the WoW hunter forums, and a post like <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=enchanterbalance&message.id=797" target="_blank" class="postlink">this</a> in the EQ enchanter forums.
<br />

<br />
I think my personal reason (and yes, I totally admit that I'm biased in Blizzard's favor) is that Sony just doesn't seem to care about enchanters much anymore. At least when there were guild summits and posts from Rytan explaining to us why none of the things we wanted would be implemented I got the impression that they cared about their game. Looking at Nadia's post, I think what helped hook me, way back when, was the impression that Brad McQuaid LOVED his game. I mean, look at that post. It's friggin' 'uge. Jeebus.
<br />

<br />
I get that same feeling from the Blizzard CR reps. Their posts bring across their frustration with themselves and their coworkers when they don't have answers for the players, their dedication to the game, and their desire to keep improving an already good product.
<br />

<br />
For some reason, <span style="color: red">(no change planned at this time)</span> vs. <span style="color: red">(currently being evaluated)</span> for the 4th month in a row doesn't really convey that to me.
<br />

<br />
And yeah, I certainly recognize that in the end, Blizzard is in the business to take my money. That in itself doesn't bother me; that's the way entertainment works. However, it becomes a problem (for me) if that's their ONLY motivation for producing the game. I don't feel like that's the case with Blizzard. Perhaps it's naive, but I genuinely feel like they care about the quality of their product.
<br />

<br />
Now, to some extent, what other people have said is true. To quote teh McQuaid:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">People get burnt out of just about anything in life. Some things take longer to grow weary of, but eventually just about everything grows old. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
And that's certainly part of it - EQ held my attention for a long time, but eventually I moved on. It was bound to happen, and both Sony and Verant certainly deserve some mad props for creating and maintaining the only computer game to hold my attention for such a long time. No doubt some of the lackluster PR from Sony is simply due to their own burnout. I can't even imagine the dedication required to stay motivated (as a programmer, designer, or PR guy) about one single project for 4+ years. I'm sure that's a factor.
<br />

<br />
But I think what it comes down to is that I was a happy EQ'er when I felt like the people at Verant/Sony cared about the game, wanted to make a balanced, enjoyable playing environment, wanted to be constantly improving things. The most excited I've been for EQ in the last 2 years is right after the Summit. I figured, hey, they're making a genuine effort. They really care about this stuff. Nowadays, though, that's not the message I get from the top ten list (essentially the only regular mode of Enchanter communication that *I've* seen for the last 3+ months; perhaps I haven't been looking hard enough). The only thing I see there is "NO! PLEASE DON'T GO! WE NEED YOUR $12.99/MO TO HELP FUND EQIII!"
<br />

<br />
It's hard to cut Sony any slack when I feel like they don't give a shit about their game beyond its ability to take my money. Similarly, it's hard NOT to give Blizzard slack when I feel like they're doing their damndest to produce a game that both their developers and their players will genuinely love.
<br />

<br />
Perhaps I'm an embittered EQ player who's been hoodwinked by Blizzard's PR guys. I don't know. My 2cp.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
